cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on enhancing network security protocols using network coding and shared capacity among working paths. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses traditional network security protocols that depend on cryptographic schemes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper uses network coding to provide data protection and data integrity against network attackers and eavesdroppers. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is mentioned in the paper as one of the applications where SNEED can be incorporated. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of SNEED in an enterprise network with multiple edge disjoint paths between two core nodes.
